MENINGITIS-NIGERIA (10)
=======================
The Herald Tribune wrote...
On Thursday March 14 1996, the International Herald Tribune wrote on page 2:
"An epidemic of meningitis raging in Burkino Faso for the past two months has
killed 722 people, the government said Wednesday. A statement by the state
epidemiological service said 8,252 cases had been reported. Further east, in
northern Nigeria, at least 2,550 people, mostly youths, have died of
meningitis since January. More than 200 people have also died in Niger.
(Reuters)"
[Moderator: Charles H. Calisher <ccalisher@vines.colostate.edu> Arthropod-
borne and Infectious Diseases Laboratory, Colorado State University, Fort
Collins, CO 80523: TEL: (970) 491-8604; FAX (970) 491-8323]

